serpent, there is room for the Spirit, and the leading is really spiritually in the assembly -- it is into Canaan. In the wilderness proper, the leading is by the cloud and the tabernacle. In my public movements I am regulated by where God is, by the cloud; but inwardly, from @Numbers 21 onwards, the tabernacle is not much in view; it is the Spirit, and the great objective is the land, entering into Canaan, which for us is realised in the assembly. I think the verse, "For as many as are led by the Spirit of God" @Romans 8: 14 finds its answer more in the assembly than in my outward relations, which relate to where God is known by the pillar of cloud.
